291
00:25:54,930 --> 00:25:56,014
God.

292
00:26:00,352 --> 00:26:03,480
Hey. Hey, hey.

293
00:26:03,564 --> 00:26:04,648
I'm sorry.

294
00:26:05,607 --> 00:26:08,277
Okay? That wasn't cool.I didn't mean that.

295
00:26:08,360 --> 00:26:09,778
-Yeah.-Hilde-- Hilde.

296
00:26:20,789 --> 00:26:22,833
Help your sister out a little.Help your sister!

297
00:26:22,916 --> 00:26:24,710
Okay. I heard you.

298
00:26:24,793 --> 00:26:26,587
Have a great day, honey. Love you.

299
00:26:26,670 --> 00:26:27,671
Yep.

300
00:26:51,820 --> 00:26:54,948
I mean, she just comes hereand starts shit out of nowhere.

301
00:26:55,032 --> 00:26:56,450
There she is.

302
00:27:06,460 --> 00:27:07,586
What a weirdo.

303
00:27:08,170 --> 00:27:10,881
I've had 20 calls this morningfrom angry parents.

304
00:27:10,964 --> 00:27:13,800
I don't know what things are likein New York, but this is a quiet town.

305
00:27:13,884 --> 00:27:17,262
And it's developmentally inappropriatefor her age.

306
00:27:17,346 --> 00:27:20,474
Yeah, with all due respect,Hilde is an unusual case.

307
00:27:20,557 --> 00:27:24,061
With all due respect, every parentthinks their child is exceptional.

308
00:27:24,561 --> 00:27:27,439
But at this school,Hilde is like any other kid.

309
00:27:27,856 --> 00:27:30,901
If she breaks the rules,she has to face the consequences.

310
00:27:30,984 --> 00:27:33,445
Listen, I may have yogurt on my shirt,

311
00:27:33,862 --> 00:27:37,366
and I look like I haven't--I haven't showered in a week because,

312
00:27:37,449 --> 00:27:39,201
you know, I haven't.

313
00:27:40,077 --> 00:27:43,455
But I'm also a former public defender,so I know a thing or two about rules,

314
00:27:43,539 --> 00:27:45,958
and my daughter has not brokenany of them.

315
00:27:46,375 --> 00:27:52,089
I'm sure her extracurricular activitieshave been inconvenient for you,

316
00:27:52,172 --> 00:27:56,343
but my guess is that you're firingthis trumped-up warning shot across my bow

317
00:27:56,426 --> 00:27:58,470
so that when you feel likepursuing disciplinary action,

318
00:27:58,554 --> 00:27:59,763
you'll have a proper paper trail.

319
00:27:59,847 --> 00:28:01,515
-Is that about right?-Mrs. Lisko.

320
00:28:01,890 --> 00:28:02,891
Bridget.

321
00:28:03,475 --> 00:28:06,019
Hey. What are you in for?

322
00:28:07,354 --> 00:28:09,815
-I'm---Just-- Just kidding.

323
00:28:09,898 --> 00:28:12,192
I totally read your article. I'm Donny.

324
00:28:13,026 --> 00:28:15,487
-I'm---But maybe we should pretend

325
00:28:15,571 --> 00:28:18,824
you don't know me for a couple of days,maybe a week, you know?

326
00:28:18,907 --> 00:28:20,325
Until this whole thing blows over.

327
00:28:22,536 --> 00:28:23,745
Fair enough.

328
00:28:24,538 --> 00:28:27,040
What about you? What'd you do?

329
00:28:34,256 --> 00:28:35,966
You feelin' the wiggle?

330
00:28:36,049 --> 00:28:39,052
That's the best part. That's the stuff.

331
00:28:39,136 --> 00:28:42,222
You and I both know that the worldisn't always kind to troublemakers.

332
00:28:42,306 --> 00:28:43,849
Especially little girls.

333
00:28:44,433 --> 00:28:46,435
If a little boy did what Hilde did,he wouldn't be in trouble.

334
00:28:46,518 --> 00:28:47,811
He would be the school president.

335
00:28:47,895 --> 00:28:51,857
Your daughter made up a storyabout a woman being murdered.

336
00:28:51,940 --> 00:28:55,736
My daughter writes a newspaperin her spare time.

337
00:28:56,361 --> 00:29:01,366
She is nine years old,and she has a passion in life.

338
00:29:02,075 --> 00:29:04,703
She has work that she lovesmore than anything else.

339
00:29:04,786 --> 00:29:06,413
I never had that,

340
00:29:06,496 --> 00:29:09,708
and I am guessing by that half-assedinspirational cat poster

341
00:29:09,791 --> 00:29:10,876
that you didn't either.

342
00:29:10,959 --> 00:29:13,378
You mean the poster my colleaguesgot me as a present

343
00:29:13,462 --> 00:29:15,547
when the school board finallygave me this job

344
00:29:15,631 --> 00:29:18,383
after offering it to two menwho were far less qualified than me?

345
00:29:18,467 --> 00:29:21,678
So, yeah, I know all about being a girl.

346
00:29:26,016 --> 00:29:27,059
I'm sorry.

347
00:29:28,393 --> 00:29:30,604
You're right. But you don't know Hilde.

348
00:29:31,939 --> 00:29:34,691
She's not like any other kid.She's my kid.

349
00:29:35,567 --> 00:29:36,735
And I'm her mom.

350
00:29:37,778 --> 00:29:39,363
So no matter how tired I am,

351
00:29:39,947 --> 00:29:42,241
or how exhausting it can beto deal with someone

352
00:29:42,324 --> 00:29:45,118
who is so tiny and so driven,

353
00:29:45,202 --> 00:29:49,081
I am going to make damn surenobody crushes her dreams.

354
00:29:55,087 --> 00:29:57,381
Well, both problem setswere exactly the same.

355
00:29:57,464 --> 00:29:58,799
Because she copied off me.

356
00:29:59,132 --> 00:30:01,510
Yeah. I'm gonna sayyou copied off her, okay?

357
00:30:01,593 --> 00:30:05,639
Thanks, Baby Einstein.You can leave now. Bye!

358
00:30:05,722 --> 00:30:07,558
But it's not the truth.

359
00:30:08,225 --> 00:30:10,686
Who cares? What are you gonna do about it?

360
00:30:10,769 --> 00:30:12,813
Write an article about mein your stupid little paper?

361
00:30:13,230 --> 00:30:16,066
You know what? Go ahead.Any press is good press.

362
00:30:25,367 --> 00:30:26,368
Hilde.

363
00:30:38,338 --> 00:30:43,135
<i>Life is not alwaysabout chasing the story, okay?</i>

364
00:30:43,218 --> 00:30:45,596
<i>Hilde, I thought you said you weregonna stop this once you got here.</i>

365
00:30:45,679 --> 00:30:47,139
<i>You know, so you can be normal.</i>

366
00:30:47,222 --> 00:30:48,640
<i>Hilde, not now.</i>

367
00:30:48,724 --> 00:30:51,602
<i>Why can't you just be a little kidfor once in your life?</i>

368
00:30:57,941 --> 00:30:59,902
<i>You guys are probably pretty tired, right?</i>

369
00:31:00,652 --> 00:31:02,988
<i>Well, you should be. Go on home.</i>

370
00:31:03,655 --> 00:31:06,575
<i>Get a nice, hot bath.Rest up 15 minutes.</i>

371
00:31:06,658 --> 00:31:08,785
<i>Then get your asses back in gear.</i>

372
00:31:36,730 --> 00:31:38,232
My name's Hilde Lisko.

373
00:31:38,315 --> 00:31:41,401
Sergeant Miller's kid already came bywith the Thin Mints.

374
00:31:42,236 --> 00:31:45,531
No. I wanna see a copyof the police report

375
00:31:45,614 --> 00:31:48,867
for the incident at 215 Oakdale Ave.

376
00:31:49,326 --> 00:31:51,787
Uh-huh. You need to settle down.

377
00:31:51,870 --> 00:31:55,791
Why can't I see the police report?It's a matter of public record.

378
00:31:55,874 --> 00:31:57,251
Why aren't you at school?

379
00:31:57,334 --> 00:31:59,878
Because crime doesn't careif it's third period.

380
00:31:59,962 --> 00:32:01,880
Hello again, little lady.

381
00:32:03,340 --> 00:32:04,466
I'm not going away.

382
00:32:07,344 --> 00:32:08,470
Can someone deal with this?

383
00:32:09,137 --> 00:32:11,348
I warned her. I explained to her--

384
00:32:11,431 --> 00:32:13,642
Nevertheless, I persisted.

385
00:32:13,725 --> 00:32:17,479
Okay, Senator. Come with me.

386
00:32:23,694 --> 00:32:26,405
All right. So, sit.

387
00:32:26,989 --> 00:32:29,658
Hold on. Let me get this for you.

388
00:32:30,117 --> 00:32:32,911
Sit right there. Sit.

389
00:32:36,039 --> 00:32:40,544
You know you can get into a lot of troublesaying something is murder when it isn't.

390
00:32:40,627 --> 00:32:44,381
Well, by the way people are acting,looks like I was right.

391
00:32:47,259 --> 00:32:49,595
I need to see the Penny Gillis file.

392
00:32:53,348 --> 00:32:55,100
No, I can't do that.

393
00:32:56,101 --> 00:32:57,853
You girls crack the case yet?

394
00:33:02,900 --> 00:33:06,445
You know what? I changed my mind.

395
00:33:08,155 --> 00:33:09,489
I'm gonna get you that file.

396
00:33:11,325 --> 00:33:13,827
I can't show you everything,but here's what I got.

397
00:33:38,852 --> 00:33:39,895
Something's missing.

398
00:33:41,104 --> 00:33:43,106
It was a machine on the table,

399
00:33:43,190 --> 00:33:47,402
and it was, like, right here.

400
00:33:50,072 --> 00:33:51,865
It looked like...

401
00:33:53,575 --> 00:33:54,576
this.

402
00:33:56,036 --> 00:33:57,287
A VCR?

403
00:33:57,371 --> 00:33:58,330
Yes.

404
00:33:59,081 --> 00:34:00,457
What's a VCR?

405
00:34:01,792 --> 00:34:03,544
-It's horrible.-It's not good.

406
00:34:03,627 --> 00:34:06,630
"This article, or paper,or whatever you call it, is so lame."

407
00:34:06,713 --> 00:34:07,756
Oh, that's not good.

408
00:34:12,052 --> 00:34:13,971
-Keep---"Doesn't this girl have parents?"

409
00:34:14,054 --> 00:34:16,931
I mean, come on.You know what? Turn off the comments.

410
00:34:17,014 --> 00:34:18,475
She doesn't need to see this.

411
00:34:18,559 --> 00:34:22,145
Look, I'm gonna print it out first,just in case.

412
00:34:22,228 --> 00:34:23,605
In case what?

413
00:34:23,688 --> 00:34:26,859
Well, remember whenI got all those death threats?

414
00:34:28,110 --> 00:34:30,737
Yeah, you taught me,always hold onto corroborating evidence.

415
00:34:31,530 --> 00:34:32,739
Death threats?

416
00:34:32,822 --> 00:34:34,408
Matt, this is our kid.

417
00:34:35,449 --> 00:34:38,620
You know, maybe we just needto tell her she needs to stop doing this.

418
00:34:39,371 --> 00:34:41,790
Bridge, come on.That's not gonna do any good.

